# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Visitor Intelligence (Workstream C) — COLLECTOR-DRIVEN cutover, fail-closed.
# There is NO Vercel env var to set for go-live. The emitter + consent scripts
# load unconditionally but self-gate at runtime: on load they fetch same-origin
# /vi-config (rewritten to the collector's /config) ONCE and stay completely
# dark — no banner, no events, no cookies — unless it returns {enabled:true}.
# The collector's /config is therefore the master on/off switch; flip it there.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# OPTIONAL local override of the first-party collector origin. Production
# defaults to the hardcoded literal https://collect.louislawgroup.com in
# next.config.mjs (so nothing depends on a Vercel env var). Only set this for
# local dev / staging against a different collector. No trailing slash.
# The browser always talks same-origin: next.config.mjs rewrites
#   /collect   -> ${COLLECTOR_ORIGIN}/collect
#   /vi-config -> ${COLLECTOR_ORIGIN}/config
# COLLECTOR_ORIGIN=https://collect.louislawgroup.com
